<h1>URIs For Common Software Purposes</h1>
<h2>XSLT related</h2>
<h3>The purpose of a transform</h3>
<p>Generally an XSLT transform transforms a document from one <code>nature</code> into another. 
We may use a convention that the <code>purpose</code> of an XSLT transform is the <code>nature</code> of what results. 
The <code>nature</code> of what is to be transformed can be described by the URI reference from which the RDDL document is obtained (i.e. the namespace URI of what is being transformed).</p>
<p>By employing this convention we can identify a transform of "A" -> "B" by looking in the RDDL document of the namespace "A" for a <code>resource</code> having a <code>purpose</code> of the namespace "B". 
(The nature of this resource will be <code>http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform</code> indicating that it is an XSLT transform.)</p>
<rddl:resource 
	id="xslt-extension"
	xlink:role="http://www.rddl.org/purposes#software-module"
